1 (iv) Identify the ground lease by stating:
2 1. The name of the original lessor;
3 2. The date the ground lease was recorded; and
4 3. The office, docket or book, and page where the ground
5 lease is recorded.
6 [(2)] (3) (I) The landlord shall mail the notice by certified mail return
7 receipt requested to the mortgagee at the address stated in the recorded request for notice
8 of judgment.
9 (II) If the notice is not given, judgment in favor of the landlord does
10 not impair the lien of the mortgagee.
11 (III) Except as otherwise provided in this subsection, the property is
12 discharged from the lease and the rights of all persons claiming under the lease are
13 foreclosed unless, within 6 calendar months after execution of the judgment for possession,
14 the tenant or any other person claiming under the lease:
15 [(i)] 1. Pays the ground rent, arrears, and all costs awarded
16 against that person; and
17 [(ii)] 2. Commences a proceeding to obtain relief from the
18 judgment.
19 (d) This section does not bar the right of any mortgagee of the lease, or any part
20 of the lease, who is not in possession at any time before expiration of 6 calendar months
21 after execution of the judgment awarding the landlord possession, to pay all costs and
22 damages sustained by the landlord and to perform all the covenants and agreements that
23 are to be performed by the tenant.
24 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
25 October 1, 2025.

